  "title": "Opioid use for chronic pain: Part 2",
  "abstract": "Opioid use for chronic pain: Part 2 Norm Buckley and Jason Busse from the Michael G. DeGroote Institute for Pain Research &amp; Care in Canada probe the effectiveness of opioid use in Canada as a treatment for chronic noncancer pain. Current best estimates suggest that 12% of individuals with chronic noncancer pain will achieve meaningful pain relief with opioids; however, there is a disconnect between the evidence for effectiveness and the ubiquity of opioid prescribing in North America.",
